column5: Someone at work just sent me this photo taken from their past weekend at the cottage.  Pretty cool.    reefrunner
Cool,  I always love those shots. They are a metaphor for life.  What happened next?
A little bugle sounded with sympathy...  wa wa wa waaaaaaaaaaa.lol
Thats pretty sweet. I wish that would happen to me one time!
At our cottage the end result would be guests having a choice of pickerel or pike fillet, pike landed by Easton
Pretty cool pic for sure.  It would seem fair to say either way the end result is that the pickerel is toast  Joey

i was on scugog once and had a stringer with about 3 nice wallys on it. i noticed the string jerking and thrashing and i looked in horror to see about a 20 pound musky mauling one of my pickeral their was 2 casualties of my walleye and the musky slowly swam away it was wild.
There's days on the French River where you can't get a walleye in without a pike crushing it. Makes me wonder why there aren't more big walleye coloured pike/musky baits.
i also had that happen on the french river. Pretty cool.
